Bruce was only kept from getting to Poyet by the intervention of assistant referee Stuart Burt and he was formally reminded of his responsibilities on Thursday.

Poyet, however, was charged by the FA, although Sportsmail understands it is likely he will be fined rather than hit with a touchline ban.

He refused to apologise for his behaviour following the game but will accept the charge of improper conduct, to which he must respond by 6pm on Monday.

